"Extremity"="LIMB"

"Paraspinal"="PARASPINAL REGION"

variables.name: TULAT
variables.label: Laterality

[TUTL1] & [TUTL2] & [TUNTL1] & [TUNTL2] & [TUNL]: set to "LEFT" if index "Left" in TUORG, set to "RIGHT" if index "Right" in TUORG, set to "BILATERAL" if index "Bilateral" in TUORG.
[CNS1] & [CNS2]: set to "LEFT" if index "Left" in CNSLOC, set to "RIGHT" if index "Right" in CNSLOC, set to "BILATERAL" if index "Bilateral" in CNSLOC.
[CNS3] & [CNS4] & [CNS5] & [CNS6]: set to "LEFT" if index "Left" in CNSLOC2, set to "RIGHT" if index "Right" in CNSLOC2, set to "BILATERAL" if index "Bilateral" in CNSLOC2.

variables.name: CNYFUNAM
variables.label: Country Full Name
variables.derivation:
Set to "China" if COUNTRY = "CHN".
Set to "Canada" if COUNTRY = "CAN".
Set to "United States of America" if COUNTRY = "USA".
Set to "France" if COUNTRY = "FRA".
Set to "Italy" if COUNTRY = "ITA".
Set to "Spain" if COUNTRY = "ESP".
Set to "United Kingdom" if COUNTRY = "GBR".

variables.name: REGION
variables.label: Geographic Region
variables.derivation:
If COUNTRY = "CHN" then REGION = "Asia".
If COUNTRY in ("FRA",  "ITA",  "ESP",  "GBR") then REGION = "Europe".
If COUNTRY in ('CAN',  'USA') then REGION = "North America".

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Exact match in ADaM v1.3 - ADSL.TRTSTM (100%)

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Exact match in ADaM v1.3 - ADSL.TRTSDTM (100%)

variables.name: TRTDUR
variables.label: Study Treatment Duration
variables.derivation:
(End Date - Date of First Exposure to Treatment)/30.4375.
End Date is the earliest date of End of Study Date (EOSDT) +1, Data Extraction Date (DEXTRDT) +1, and Date of Last Exposure to Treatment (TRTEDT) +21.

variables.name: EOTDT
variables.label: End of Treatment Date (N)
variables.derivation: For subjects who were randomized (RANDFL = "Y"), set to DS.DSSTDTC where DS.DSCAT = "DISPOSITION EVENT" and DS.DSSCAT = "END OF TREATMENT", converted to SAS date.

variables.name: EOTSTT
variables.label: End of Treatment Status

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Exact match in ADaM v1.3 - ADSL.EOTSTT (100%)

variables.name: DCTREAS
variables.label: Reason for Discontinuation of Treatment
variables.derivation: For subjects who completed (EOTSTT = "COMPLETED") or discontinued (EOTSTT = "DISCONTINUED") study treatment, set to DS.DSDECOD where DS.DSCAT = "DISPOSITION EVENT" and DS.DSSCAT = "END OF TREATMENT"; set to "SIGNIFICANT PROTOCOL DEVIATION" when DS.DSDECOD = "PROTOCOL DEVIATION". Else set to null.

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Exact match in ADaM v1.3 - ADSL.DCTREAS (100%)

variables.name: DCTREASP
variables.label: Reason Specify for Discont of Treatment
variables.derivation: For subjects who discontinued study treatment (EOTSTT = "DISCONTINUED"), set to DS.DSTERM where DS.DSCAT = "DISPOSITION EVENT" and DS.DSSCAT = "END OF TREATMENT" and DS.DSDECOD in ("OTHER", "PROTOCOL DEVIATION").

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Exact match in ADaM v1.3 - ADSL.DCTREASP (100%)

variables.name: EOSDT
variables.label: End of Study Date
variables.derivation: For subjects who were randomized (RANDFL = "Y"), set to DS.DSSTDTC where DS.DSCAT = "DISPOSITION EVENT" and DS.DSSCAT= "END OF STUDY", converted to SAS date.

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Exact match in ADaM v1.3 - ADSL.EOSDT (100%)

variables.name: EOSSTT

variables.derivation: For subjects who were randomized (RANDFL = "Y"), set to "DISCONTINUED" if DS.DSCAT = "DISPOSITION EVENT" and DS.DSSCAT = "END OF STUDY" and DS.DSDECOD is not missing; else if subject does not have END OF STUDY record in SDTM.DS and not died (DTHFL NE "Y") then set to "ONGOING". Else if subject died then set to "DISCONTINUED".

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Exact match in ADaM v1.3 - ADSL.EOSSTT (100%)

variables.label: Reason for Discontinuation from Study
variables.derivation: For subjects who were randomized (RANDFL = "Y"), set to DS.DSDECOD where DS.DSCAT = "DISPOSITION EVENT" and DS.DSSCAT= "END OF STUDY"; else set to null if EOSSTT = "ONGOING".

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Exact match in ADaM v1.3 - ADSL.DCSREAS (100%)

variables.name: DCSREASP
variables.label: Reason Spec for Discont from Study
variables.derivation: Set to DS.DSTERM where DS.DSCAT = "DISPOSITION EVENT" and DS.DSSCAT= "END OF STUDY" and DS.DSDECOD = "OTHER".

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Exact match in ADaM v1.3 - ADSL.DCSREASP (100%)

variables.name: NEWATDTC
variables.label: Start Date of New Anti-Cancer Therapy
variables.derivation: For subjects who received sebsequent anticancer therapy (CM.CMCAT = "FOLLOW-UP CANCER THERAPY"), set to the earliest non-missing CM.CMSTDTC for each subject. Else set to null.

variables.name: NEWATDT
variables.label: Start Date of New Anti-Cancer Thrpy. (N)
variables.derivation:
ADSL.NEWATDTC converted to SAS date.
Rules of date imputation for records with partial dates (CM.CMSTDTC where CM.CMCAT = "FOLLOW-UP CANCER THERAPY): 
1. When year and month are present and day is missing: if the year and month are the same as ADSL.TRTEDT, then set NEWATDT to TRTEDT+1; otherwise, set day to the 15th day of the month.
2. When year is present and month and day are missing: if the year is the same as the year of ADSL.TRTEDT, then set NEWATDT to TRTEDT+1; otherwise impute month and day to June 30th.
After partial dates imputation according to the rules, select the earliest NEWATDT. If the imputed NEWATDT is later than the CM.CMENDTC of the same record and the CM.CMENDTC is not imputed, then set NEWATDT to the CM.CMENDTC converted to SAS date.

variables.name: NEWATDTF
variables.label: Start Date of New Anti-Cancer Imp. Flag

codelist_values.decode: Month Imputed: Month and day are imputed
Year Imputed: Entire date (year, month and day) is imputed

variables.derivation:
NEWATDTF = 'D' if the day value within the character date is imputed.
NEWATDTF = 'M' if the month value and the day value within the character date are imputed.
Note that only incompleted day values or month values needed to be imputed for this study.

variables.name: LSALVDTC
variables.label: Date of Last Known Alive
variables.derivation: ADSL.LSALVDT converted to character value in ISO 8601 date format

variables.name: LSALVDT
variables.label: Date of Last Known Alive (N)
variables.derivation:
1. For subjects who died, set to ADSL.DTHDTC converted to SAS date if DTHDTC presents a complete date value. Else proceed to steps 2 and 3.
For remaining subjects: 
2. Get the last known alive date from Survival Status (SUPPSS.QVAL where QNAM = "LSTALDTC" from the latest Survival Follow-up).
3. Get the latest complete date from all SDTM domains except DM, DS, DD, DV, SE, SV, SU, MH, PR, and SS. 
Compare date values from steps 2 and 3 then set LSALVDT to the maximum converted to SAS date.

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Name match in SDTM v3.4 (defined in DM) (85%)
CDISC auto-approved: Name match in SDTM v3.4 (defined in DM) (85%)

variables.name: DTHDT
variables.label: Date of Death
variables.derivation:
DM.DTHDTC converted to SAS date. 
Rules of date imputation for DM.DTHDTC with partial date:
1. When year and month are present and day is missing: if the year and month are the same as ADSL.LSALVDT, then set DTHDT to LSALVDT+1; otherwise set day to 15th day of the month. 
2. When year is present and month and day are missing: if the year is the same as the year of ADSL.LSALVDT, then set DTHDT to LSALVDT+1; otherwise imput month and day to June 30th.

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Exact match in ADaM v1.3 - ADSL.DTHDT (100%)

variables.name: DTHDTF
variables.label: Date of Death Imputation Flag

codelist_values.decode: Month Imputed: Month and day are imputed
Year Imputed: Entire date (year, month and day) is imputed

variables.derivation:
DTHDTF = 'D' if the day value within the character date is imputed.
DTHDTF = 'M' if the month value and the day value within the character date are imputed.
Note that only incompleted day values or month values needed to be imputed for this study.

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Exact match in ADaM v1.3 - ADSL.DTHDTF (100%)

variables.name: LAD30FL
variables.label: Death Flag in 30 Days after Last Dose
variables.derivation: For subjects who received at least one dose of study treatment and died, set to "Y" if ADSL.TRTSDT <= ADSL.DTHDT <= min(ADSL.TRTEDT+30, ADSL.NEWATDT); else set to null.

variables.name: LAD90FL
variables.label: Death Flag in 90 Days after Last Dose
variables.derivation: For subjects who received at least one dose of study treatment and died, set to "Y" if ADSL.TRTSDT <= ADSL.DTHDT <= min(ADSL.TRTEDT+90, ADSL.NEWATDT); else set to null.

variables.name: AFT90FL
variables.label: Death Flag after 90 Days after Last Dose
variables.derivation: For subjects who received at least one dose of study treatment and died, set to "Y" if ADSL.DTHDT > min(ADSL.TRTEDT+90, ADSL.NEWATDT); else set to null.

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Exact match in ADaM v1.3 - ADSL.DTHCAUS (100%)

variables.name: INIDGDTC
variables.label: Tumor Initial Diagnosis Date
variables.derivation: FA.FADTC where FA.FACAT = "TUMOR DIAGNOSIS" and FA.FATESTCD = "CELLCAR"

variables.name: INIDGDT
variables.label: Tumor Initial Diagnosis Date (N)
variables.derivation:
ADSL.INIDGDTC converted to SAS date.
Rules of date imputation for partial dates of ADSL.INIDGDTC:
1. If year and month are present and day is missing: set day to 15th day of the month.
2. If year is present and month and day are missing: set month and day to June 30th.
3. If INIDGDTC is completely missing, then set INIDGDT to non-missing ADSL.TRTSDT. 
If the imputed INIDGDT is greater than non-missing TRTSDT then set INIDGDT to TRTSDT.

variables.name: INIDGDTF
variables.label: Tumor Diagnosis Date Imputation Flag
variables.derivation:
INIDGDTF = "Y" if year and month and day in INIDGDT are imputed.
INIDGDTF = "M' if month and day in INIDGDT are imputed.
INIDGDTF = "D" if day in INIDGDT is imputed.

variables.name: INIDGDUR
variables.label: Duration - Tumor Diagnosis to Rand.(mon)
variables.derivation: For subjects who were randomized with non-missing ADSL.INIDGDT, set to (ADSL.RANDDT - ADSL.INIDGDT + 1)/30.4375.

variables.name: ERFSTAG
variables.label: Clinical Stage at Study Entry
variables.derivation:
ERFSTAG = "IIIB" if FA.FATESTCD = "CLISTG" and FA.FASTRESC = "Stage IIIB".  
ERFSTAG = "IIIC" if FA.FATESTCD = "CLISTG" and FA.FASTRESC = "Stage IIIC".  
ERFSTAG = "IV" if FA.FATESTCD = "CLISTG" and FA.FASTRESC = "Stage IV".  
ERFSTAG = "IVA" if FA.FATESTCD = "CLISTG" and FA.FASTRESC = "Stage IVA".  
ERFSTAG = "IVB" if FA.FATESTCD = "CLISTG" and FA.FASTRESC = "Stage IVB".  
ERFSTAG = "Unknown" if FA.FATESTCD = "CLISTG" and FA.FASTRESC = "Unknown".

variables.name: METFL
variables.label: Baseline Metastase Flag
variables.derivation: METFL = "Y" if ADSL.BRAINMET = "Yes" or ADSL.LIVEMET = "Yes" or ADSL.BONMET = "Yes" or ADSL.KIDAGMET = "Yes" or ADSL.METOTH = "Yes"; else set to null.

variables.name: METNUM
variables.label: Number of Distant Metastases
variables.derivation: Count distinct  non-missing FA.FALOC per subject when FA.FATESTCD = "METAST" and FA.FASTRESC = "Yes".

variables.name: BRAINMET
variables.label: Brain Metastase
variables.derivation: BRAINMET = "Yes" if FA.FATESTCD = "METAST" and FA.FASTRESC = "Yes" and FA.FALOC = "BRAIN".

variables.name: LIVEMET
variables.label: Liver Metastase
variables.derivation: LIVEMET = "Yes" if FA.FATESTCD = "METAST" and FA.FASTRESC = "Yes" and FA.FALOC = "LIVER".

variables.name: BONMET
variables.label: Bone Metastase
variables.derivation: BONMET = "Yes" if FA.FATESTCD = "METAST" and FA.FASTRESC = "Yes" and FA.FALOC in ("BONE/BONE MARROW", "CERVICAL SPINE", "LUMBAR SPINE", "PELVIC BONE", "PELVIS", "RIB", "RIB(S), LEFT", "RIB(S), RIGHT", "RIBS, BILATERAL", "SKULL", "THORACIC SPINE").

variables.name: KIDAGMET
variables.label: Kidney Metastase
variables.derivation: KIDAGMET = "Yes" if FA.FATESTCD = "METAST" and FA.FASTRESC = "Yes" and FA.FALOC in ("KIDNEY, LEFT", "KIDNEY",  "KIDNEY, RIGHT", "KIDNEYS, BILATERAL", "RENAL PELVIS", "ADRENAL GLANDS, BILATERAL", "ADRENAL, LEFT", "ADRENAL GLAND", "ADRENAL, RIGHT").

variables.name: METOTH
variables.label: Other Metastase
variables.derivation: METOTH = "Yes" if FA.FATESTCD = "METAST" and FA.FASTRESC = "Yes" and ADSL.BRAINMET ne "Yes" and ADSL.LIVEMET ne "Yes" and ADSL.BONMET ne "Yes" and ADSL.KIDAGMET ne "Yes".

variables.name: SMOKSTT
variables.label: Smoking Status
variables.derivation:
SMOKSTT = "Former" if SU.SUTRT = "SMOKE" and SU.SUOCCUR = "Y" and SU.SUENRTPT = "BEFORE". 
SMOKSTT = "Current" if SU.SUTRT = "SMOKE" and SU.SUOCCUR = "Y" and SU.SUENRPTP = "BEFORE". 
SMOKSTT = "Never" if SUSUTRT = "SMOKE" and SU.SUOCCUR = "N".

variables.name: EGFRMTFL
variables.label: Baseline EGFR Mutation Flag
variables.derivation: Set to "Y" if there were any EGFR mutation(s) of ADSL.S19DEL, ADSL.L858R, ADSL.G719X, ADSL.S768I, ADSL.T790M, ADSL.L861Q, and/or ADSL.EGFROTH.

variables.name: S19DEL
variables.label: EGFR Mutation Site - 19DEL
variables.derivation:
1. Derive variable GFREFO (Other EGFR Mutation Site) from analysis dataset egfroth.sas7bdat (EFGROTH.MISPECO), with variables of subject ID and MAPPING. 
2. Merge analysis dataset EGFROTH with SDTM.GF domain by GFREFO (SUPPGF.QVAL where SUPPGF.QNAM = "GFREFO"), then redefine GF.GFREFID for EFGR mutation sites as "19Del", "G719X", "Other", or "19Del/Other" per EGFROTH.MAPPING value. 
3. Set S19DEL to GF.GFSTRESC when GF.GFTESTCD = "EGFRM" and (GF.GFREFID or redefined GFREFID) is "19Del"; if GF.GFSTRESC = "Other" and GF.GFORRES = "MUTATED" then set S19DEL to "Positive".

variables.name: L858R
variables.label: EGFR Mutation Site - L858R
variables.derivation: Set L858R to GF.GFSTRESC where GF.GFTESTCD = "EGFRM" and GF.GFREFID = "L858R"; if GF.GFSTRESC = "Other" and GF.GFORRES = "MUTATED" then set L858R to "Positive".

variables.name: G719X
variables.label: EGFR Mutation Site - G719X
variables.derivation:
1. Derive variable GFREFO (Other EGFR Mutation Site) from analysis dataset egfroth.sas7bdat (EFGROTH.MISPECO), with variables of subject ID and MAPPING. 
2. Merge analysis dataset EGFROTH with SDTM.GF domain by GFREFO (SUPPGF.QVAL where SUPPGF.QNAM = "GFREFO"), then redefine GF.GFREFID for EFGR mutation sites as "19Del", "G719X", "Other", or "19Del/Other" per EGFROTH.MAPPING value. 
3. Set G719X to GF.GFSTRESC when GF.GFTESTCD = "EGFRM" and (GF.GFREFID or redefined GFREFID) is "G719X"; if GF.GFSTRESC = "Other" and GF.GFORRES = "MUTATED" then set G719X to "Positive".

variables.name: S768I
variables.label: EGFR Mutation Site - S768I
variables.derivation: Set S761I to GF.GFSTRESC where GF.GFTESTCD = "EGFRM" and GF.GFREFID = "S761I"; if GF.GFSTRESC = "Other" and GF.GFORRES = "MUTATED" then set S761I to "Positive".

variables.name: T790M
variables.label: EGFR Mutation Site - T790M
variables.derivation: Set T790M to GF.GFSTRESC where  (GF.GFTESTCD in ("EGFRM", "EGFRTM") and GF.GFREFID = "T790M"); if GF.GFSTRESC = "Other" and GF.GFORRES = "MUTATED" then set T790M to "Positive".

variables.name: L861Q
variables.label: EGFR Mutation Site - L861Q
variables.derivation: Set L861Q to GF.GFSTRESC where GF.GFTESTCD = "EGFRM" and GF.GFREFID = "L861Q"; if GF.GFSTRESC = "Other" and GF.GFORRES = "MUTATED" then set L861Q to "Positive".

variables.name: EGFROTH
variables.label: EGFR Mutation Site - Other
variables.derivation:
1. Derive variable GFREFO (Other EGFR Mutation Site) from analysis dataset egfroth.sas7bdat (EFGROTH.MISPECO), with variables of subject ID and MAPPING. 
2. Merge analysis dataset EGFROTH with SDTM.GF domain by GFREFO (SUPPGF.QVAL where SUPPGF.QNAM = "GFREFO"), then redefine GF.GFREFID for EFGR mutation sites as "19Del", "G719X", "Other", or "19Del/Other" per EGFROTH.MAPPING value. 
3. Set EGFROTH to GF.GFSTRESC when GF.GFTESTCD = "EGFRM" and (GF.GFREFID or redefined GFREFID) is "Other"; if GF.GFSTRESC = "Other" and GF.GFORRES = "MUTATED" then set EGFROTH to "Positive".

variables.name: FIREGFR
variables.label: First Gen. EGFR-TKI Therapy
variables.derivation:
1. Merge SDTM.CM domain with analysis dataset PRPIRGER by CMTRT.
2. FIREGFR = "Y" if CM.CMCAT = "PRIOR CANCER THERAPY" and (SUPPCM.QVAL = "Locally Advanced or Recurrent or Metastasis" where QNAM = "CMREAS") and PRPIRGER.GENCAT = "1st".

variables.name: SECEGFR
variables.label: Second Gen. EGFR-TKI Therapy
variables.derivation:
1. Merge SDTM.CM domain with analysis dataset PRPIRGER by CMTRT.
2. SECEGFR = "Y" if CM.CMCAT = "PRIOR CANCER THERAPY" and (SUPPCM.QVAL = "Locally Advanced or Recurrent or Metastasis" where QNAM = "CMREAS") and PRPIRGER.GENCAT = "2nd".

variables.name: THREGFR
variables.label: Third Gen. EGFR-TKI Therapy
variables.derivation:
1. Merge SDTM.CM domain with analysis dataset PRPIRGER by CMTRT.
2. THREGFR = "Y" if CM.CMCAT = "PRIOR CANCER THERAPY" and (SUPPCM.QVAL = "Locally Advanced or Recurrent or Metastasis" where QNAM = "CMREAS") and PRPIRGER.GENCAT = "3rd".

variables.name: FOURGFR
variables.label: Fourth Gen. EGFR-TKI Therapy
variables.derivation:
1. Merge SDTM.CM domain with analysis dataset PRPIRGER by CMTRT.
2. FOURGFR = "Y" if CM.CMCAT = "PRIOR CANCER THERAPY" and (SUPPCM.QVAL = "Locally Advanced or Recurrent or Metastasis" where QNAM = "CMREAS") and PRPIRGER.GENCAT = "4th".

variables.name: LINE
variables.label: Lines. EGFR-TKI Therapy
variables.derivation:
1. Merge SDTM.CM domain with analysis dataset PRPIRGER by CMTRT.
2. Derive LINE as count distinct non-missing CM.CMGRPID where CM.CMCAT = "PRIOR CANCER THERAPY" and (SUPPCM.QVAL = "Locally Advanced or Recurrent or Metastasis" where QNAM = "CMREAS") per subject.

variables.name: PRILINE
variables.label: Line of Prior Cancer Therapy
variables.derivation:
1. Based on analysis dataset PRILINE, derive PRILINE.PRILINE by keeping digits and removing any thing else from PRILINE.MEDLINE, then sort analysis dataset PRILINE by PRILINE.USUBJID and PRILINE.PRILINE. 
2. Set ADSL.PRILINE to the last record of PRILINE.PRILINE per sort by PRILINE.USUBJID and PRILINE.PRILINE.

variables.name: PDLSG1R
variables.label: PD-L1 Tumor Proportion Score Group 1
variables.derivation:
PDLSG1R = "<1%" if non-missing ADSL.PDLSCORE <1.
PDLSG1R = ">=1%" if ADSL.PDLSCORE >=1.

variables.name: PDLSG2R
variables.label: PD-L1 Tumor Proportion Score Group 2
variables.derivation:
PDLSG2R = "<1%" if non-missing ADSL.PDLSCORE <1. 
PDLSG2R = "1-49%" if 1<=ADSL.PDLSCORE<=49.
PDLSG2R = ">=50%" if ADSL.PDLSCORE >=50.

variables.name: PRSURGFL
variables.label: Prior Cancer Surgery/Procedure Flag
variables.derivation: PRSURGFL = "Y" for subjects with PR.PRCAT = "PRIOR CANCER SURGERY / PROCEDURE" and (SUPPPR.QVAL in ("Curative", "Palliative") where QNAM = "PRREAS").

variables.name: PRRADFL
variables.label: Prior Radiotherapy Flag
variables.derivation: PRRADFL = "Y" for subjects with PR.PRCAT = "PRIOR RADIOTHERAPY and PR.PROCCUR = "Y".

variables.name: EGFR
variables.label: Baseline Est. Glomerular Filtration Rate
variables.derivation:
1. Derive Serum Creatinine at Baseline in mg/dL: CREATBL = LB.LBSTRESN*0.0113 (when LB.LBTESTCD = "CREAT" and LB.LBBLFL = "Y" and LB.LBSTRESU = "umol/L").
2. Calculate eGFR per CKD-EPI equation: 
EGFR = 142 × min(Scr/κ,1)^α × max(Scr/κ, 1)^(-1.200) × 0.9938^Age × 1.012 [if female]. 
Scr is serum creatinine (mg/dL), κ is 0.7 for female and 0.9 for male, α is -0.241 for female and -0.302 for male, min indicates the minimum of Scr/κ or 1, and max indicates the maximum of Scr/κ or 1.

variables.name: HYPERBL
variables.label: Ongoing Hypertension at Baseline
variables.derivation: HYPERBL = "Y" if subject reported Hypertension Event in Medical history OR reported Hypertension Adverse event before first dose and continue after first dose. Hypertension event is defined by SMQ Hypertension with Narrow Scope.

variables.name: IAITTFL
variables.label: ITT Population at IA
variables.derivation: Set to "Y" if randomization date (ADSL.RANDDT) is before 11JUN2024 for ITT population at interim analysis (IA); else set to "N".

variables.name: IADCODT
variables.label: IA Data Cutoff Date
variables.derivation: Set to 10JUN2024 for subjects who were in the ITT population at interim analysis (ADSL.IAITTFL = "Y"); else set to missing value.

variables.name: IADTHDT
variables.label: Death Date at IA
variables.derivation:
Only derive for subjects who were included in ITT population at IA. 
Set to death date (ADSL.DTHDT) if subject died prior to IA Data Cutoff Date (ADSL.IADCODT) except for the following: if a subject was alive during the survival sweep for IA and death data records were entered in the database after IA then set IADTHDT to missing value.

variables.name: IATRTSDT
variables.label: Date of First Exposure to Trt. (IA)
variables.derivation:
Only derive for subjects who were included in ITT population at IA.
For subjects who received at least one dose of study treatment, set IATRTSDT to ADSL.TRTSDT.

variables.name: IATRTEDT
variables.label: Date of Last Exposure to Treatment at IA
variables.derivation:
Only derive for subjects who were included in ITT population at IA.
For subjects who received at least one dose of study treatment, set IATRTEDT to the last EC.ECSTDTC where the date part of the ECSTDTC is prior to 10JUN2024 and EC.ECTRT = "AK112/PLACEBO" and EC.ECMOOD = "PERFORMED" and EC.ECDOSE >0, converted to SAS date.

variables.name: IALALVDT
variables.label: Date of Last Known Alive (N) at IA
variables.derivation:
Only derive for subjects who were included in ITT population at IA. 
1. For subjects who died prior to IA Data Cutoff Date (ADSL.IADCODT), set to ADSL.DTHDTC converted to SAS date if DTHDTC presents a complete date value. Else proceed to steps 2 and 3.
For remaining subjects: 
2. Get the last known alive date from Survival Status (SUPPSS.QVAL where QNAM = "LSTALDTC" from the last Survival Follow-up prior to IA Data Cutoff Date).
3. Get the latest complete date which is prior to the IA Data Cutoff Date from all SDTM domains except DM, DS, DD, DV, SE, SV, SU, MH, PR, and SS. 
Compare date values from steps 2 and 3 then set IALALVDT to the maximum converted to SAS date.

variables.name: IAEOTDT
variables.label: End of Treatment Date (N) at IA
variables.derivation:
Only derive for subjects who were included in ITT population at IA.
For subjects who ended study treatment before IA Data Cutoff Date, set IAEOTDT to ADSL.EOTDT if non-missing EOTDT <= 10JUN2024; else set to missing value.

variables.name: IADCTREA
variables.label: Reason for Disc of Treatment at IA
variables.derivation:
Only derive for subjects who were included in ITT population at IA.
For subjects who ended study treatment before IA Data Cutoff Date, set IADCTREA to ADSL.DCTREAS if non-missing EOTDT <= 10JUN2024; else set to null.

variables.name: IAEOSDT
variables.label: End of Study Date (N) at IA
variables.derivation:
Only derive for subjects who were included in ITT population at IA.
For subjects who ended study before IA Data Cutoff Date, set IAEOSDT to ADSL.EOSDT if non-missing EOSDT <= 10JUN2024; else set to missing value.

variables.name: IATRTDUR

variables.name: ASTDT
variables.label: Analysis Start Date
variables.derivation:
AE.AESTDTC, converted to a numeric SAS date. Some events with partial dates are imputed in a conservative manner.
If the day component is missing, a value of 15th of the month is used, if both month and day are missing then set to June 30th of the year.
Each imputed date will go through logical check to make sure AE start and end dates are in proper order relative to other study milestone dates:
1. If imputed AE AE start date is after a non-imputed AE end date, then set AE start date to AE end date. 
2. If both AE start and end dates are imputed and need logical check then the date with more known information will take the priority.
3. If imputed AE  start date has same year and/or month as treatment start date and the imputed date is before  the treatment start date, then set AE start date to treatment start date.
4. If imputed AE  start date is after safety assessment date and has same year and or month as safety assessment date then set to safety assessment date. Safety assessment end date is the earliest date of TRTEDT+30 (only for subjects who discontinued treatment), new anticancer therapy start date -1, and last known alive date.

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Exact match in ADaM v1.3 - ADAE.ASTDT (100%)

variables.name: AENDT
variables.label: Analysis End Date
variables.derivation:
AE.AEENDTC, converted to a numeric SAS date. Some events with partial dates are imputed in a conservative manner.
If the day component is missing, a value of 15th of the month is used, if both month and day are missing then set to June 30th of the year.
Each imputed date will go through logical check to make sure AE start and end dates are in proper order relative to other study milestone dates:
1. If imputed AE end date is before a non-imputed AE start date, then set AE end date to AE start date.
2. If both AE start and end dates are imputed and need logical check then the date with more known information will take the priority. 
3. If imputed AE end date is before treatment start date but the year and/or month of the end date is same as treatment start date, then set AE end date to treatment start date.
4. If imputed AE end date is after the minimum of (death date, study exit date, data cutoff date), then set to the minimum of (death date, study exit date, data cutoff date).

variables.name: AVAL
variables.label: Analysis Value
variables.derivation:
The duration is calculated from the SMQ Proteinuria event (non-missing ADAE.CQ08NAM) start date to the resolved date. If multiple occurrences of the same event exist, then total duration is calculated as the sum of all occurrences. For ongoing events, the duration is censored at the earliest of the following dates: Data Cut-off Date (ADSL.DEXTRDT), Date of Last Exposure to Treatment (ADSL.TRTEDT) +30 days for non-SAE and +90 days for SAE, Date of death (ADSL.DTHDT).
For classification: If only one preferred term exists, the duration is calculated as above. If multiple AEs are present, overlapping AEs (where the start of one is on or before the end of another) are combined. The total duration is the sum of all non-overlapping AEs, excluding any gaps.

variables.name: ASTDT
variables.label: Analysis Start Date
variables.derivation:
Numeric version of date part of SDTM.CM.CMSTDTC. Partial dates will be imputed.
In general, if day is missing then impute with 15th of the month, and if both month and day are missing then set to June30 of the year.
Each imputed date will go through logical check to make sure CM start and end dates are in proper order relative to other study milestone dates.
1. If imputed CM start date is after a non-imputed CM end date, then set CM start date to CM end date.
2. If both CM start and end date are imputed and need logical check then the date with more known information will take the priority.
For records where CM.CMCAT='CONCOMITANT MEDICATION', also apply the below rules:
3. If imputed CM start date has same year and/or month as treatment start date (TRTSDT) and the imputed date is after TRTSDT, then set to TRTSDT.
4. If imputed CM start date is after safety assessment end date and the year/month is same as safety assessment date, then set to safety assessment end date.
Safety assessment end date is the earliest date of TRTEDT+30 (only for subjects who discontinued treatment), new anticancer therapy start date -1, and last known alive date.
For records where CM.CMCAT='FOLLOW-UP CANCER THERAPY', also apply the below rules:
3. If imputed CM start date has same year and/or month as TRTEDT, then set to TRTEDT+1.
4. If CMSTDTC is completely missing, set to TRTEDT+1.
5. If imputed CM start date is after last known alive date, then set to last known alive date.
For records where CM.CMCAT=’PRIOR CANCER THERAPY', also apply the below rules:
3. If imputed CM start date has same year and/or month as TRTSDT and the imputed date is after TRTSDT, then set to TRTSDT-1.

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Name match in ADaM v1.3 (defined in ADAE) (88%)

variables.name: AENDT
variables.label: Analysis End Date
variables.derivation:
Numeric version of date part of SDTM.CM.CMENDTC, Partial dates will be imputed.
In general, if day is missing then impute with 15th of the month, and if both month and day are missing then set to June30 of the year.
Each imputed date will go through logical check to make sure CM start and end dates are in proper order relative to other study milestone dates.
1. If imputed CM end date is before a non-imputed CM start date, then set CM end date to CM start date.
2. If both CM start and end date are imputed and need logical check then the date with more known information will take the priority.
For records where CM.CMCAT='CONCOMITANT MEDICATION', also apply the below rules:
3. If imputed CM end date has same year and/or month as TRTSDT and the imputed date is before TRTSDT, then set to TRTSDT.
4. If imputed CM end date is after last known alive date, then set to last known alive date.
For records where CM.CMCAT='FOLLOW-UP CANCER THERAPY', also apply the below rules:

variables.name: PRIORFL
variables.label: Prior Medications Flag
variables.derivation: Set to "Y" if medication started or stopped before exposure to study treatment. Note: Set to "Y" if CMSTDTC and CMENDTC are completing missing or CMCAT contains "PRIOR".

variables.name: CMFL
variables.label: Concomitant Medications Flag
variables.derivation:
Set to "Y" if medication are concomitant to the study treatment. 
Concomitant medications are defined as medications taken after the administration of study treatment on Study Day 1 through 30 days after last dose of study treatment or initiation of subsequent anticancer therapy - 1, whichever occurs first. This includes medications that were started before the initiation of study treatment and are ongoing during the study.
Only records from CONCOMITANT MEDICATION CRF page are considered for CMFL derivation.
Note: Set to "Y" if CMSTDTC and CMENDTC are completing missing.

variables.name: CORT1FL
variables.label: Corticosteroid Classification Flag 1
variables.derivation:
CORT1FL = "Y" when any of the following conditions are met:
1. When ATC3CD is equal to "H02A" or "H02B";
2. When ATC4CD is equal to A07EA" or "M01BA".
Note: This is a systemic steroid Flag.

variables.name: CORT2FL
variables.label: Corticosteroid Classification Flag 2

variables.name: CORT3FL
variables.label: Corticosteroid Classification Flag 3
variables.derivation:
CORT3FL = "Y" when any of the following conditions are met:
1. When ATC2CD is equal to "H03";
2. When ATC3CD is equal to H01A" or "H01B".
Note: This is the flag for endocrine therapy.

variables.name: CORT4FL
variables.label: Corticosteroid Classification Flag 4
variables.derivation:
CORT4FL = "Y" when ATC4CD is equal to "L04AA" or "L04AB.
Note: This is the flag for other immunosuppressants.

variables.name: CORT5FL
variables.label: Corticosteroid Classification Flag 5
variables.derivation:
CORT5FL = "Y" when ATC3CD is equal to H03B"Y".
Note: This is the flag of antithyroid therapy drugs.

variables.name: HYPERMFL
variables.label: Hypertensive Medication Flag
variables.derivation: HYPERMFL = "Y" if ATC2 code falls under C02 - Antihypertensives, C03 - Diuretics, C07 - Beta blocking agents, C08 - Calcium channel blockers, and C09 - Agents acting on the renin-angiotensin system.

variables.name: ANTICCAT
variables.label: Subsequent Anticancer Treatment Category
variables.derivation:
Set ANTICCAT to CMCTCAT.ANTICAT by merging ADCM and the intermediate dataset CMCTCAT by CMDECOD and ATC4; if ANTICCAT is missing then set ANTICCAT to "OTHER ANTICANCER THERAPY". 
See ADRG (SEC-4.3 Intermediate Datasets, page 3)

variables.name: AVALCAT1
variables.label: Analysis Value Category 1
variables.derivation:
AVALCAT1 = "< 3 months" if . < AVAL < 3.
AVALCAT1 = ">=3 and <6 months" if 3 <= AVAL < 6.
AVALCAT1 = ">=6 and <12 months" if 6 <= AVAL < 12.
AVALCAT1 = ">=12 and <18 months" if 12 <= AVAL < 18.
AVALCAT1 = ">=18 months" if AVAL >= 18.

variables.name: AVALCA1N
variables.label: Analysis Value Category 1 (N)
variables.derivation:
Numeric code for AVALCAT1. 
Convert character value to numeric if AVALCAT1 in ("1", "2", "3", "4").
Set to 5 if AVALCAT1 = "5-12".
Set to 6 if AVALCAT1 = "> 12".

variables.name: AVALCA1N
variables.label: Analysis Value Category 1 (N)
variables.derivation:
Numeric code for AVALCAT1. 
AVALCA1N = 1 if AVALCAT1 = "< 3 months".
AVALCA1N = 2 if AVALCAT1 = ">=3 and <6 months".
AVALCA1N = 3 if AVALCAT1 = ">=6 and <12 months".
AVALCA1N = 4 if AVALCAT1 = ">=12 and <18 months".
AVALCA1N = 5 if AVALCAT1 = ">=18 months".

variables.name: AVALCA1N
variables.label: Analysis Value Category 1 (N)

variables.name: AVAL
variables.label: Analysis Value
variables.derivation: If PARAMCD in ("ALT", "AST") then calculate R2ANRHI as non-missing AVAL/ANRHI. For a given visit, if PARAMCD in ("ALT", "AST") and either R2ANRHI >=3 then AVAL=1; otherwise if PARAMCD in ("ALT", "AST") then AVAL=0. If the visit is within 5-day window to previous visits then use the maximum R2ANRHI from visits within the 5-day window per each parameter.

variables.name: AVAL
variables.label: Analysis Value
variables.derivation: If PARAMCD = "BILI" then calculate R2ANRHI as non-missing AVAL/ANRHI. For a given visit, if PARAMCD = "BILI" and R2ANRHI >=2 then AVAL=1; else AVAL=0. If the visit is within 5-day window to previous visits then use the maximum R2ANRHI from visits within the 5-day window per each parameter.

variables.name: AVAL
variables.label: Analysis Value
variables.derivation: If PARAMCD = "ALP" then calculate R2ANRHI as non-missing AVAL/ANRHI. For a given visit, if PARAMCD = "ALP" and (. < R2ANRHI <2) then AVAL=1; else AVAL=0. If the visit is within 5-day window to previous visits then use the maximum R2ANRHI from visits within the 5-day window per each parameter.

variables.name: AVAL
variables.label: Analysis Value
variables.derivation: If PARAMCD = "BILI" then calculate R2ANRHI as non-missing AVAL/ANRHI. For a given visit, if (PARAMCD = "BILI" and R2ANRHI >=1.5) and (AVAL=1 when PARAMCD = "TRANSHY") then set AVAL=1 for this PARAM; Otherwise set AVAL =0. If the visit is within 5-day window to previous visits then use the maximum R2ANRHI from visits within the 5-day wondow per each parameter.

variables.name: AVAL
variables.label: Analysis Value
variables.derivation: For a given visit, if PARAMCD in ("TRANSHY", "BILIHY") and if both have AVAL=1 then for this PARAM then AVAL=1; Otherwise if for a given visit, if PARAMCD in ("TRANSHY", "BILIHY") then AVAL=0. If the visit is within 5-day window to previous visits then use the maximum R2ANRHI from visits within the 5-day window per each parameter.

variables.name: AVAL
variables.label: Analysis Value
variables.derivation: For a given visit, if PARAMCD in ("TRANSHY", "BILIHY", "ALPHY") and if all the three PARAMs have AVAL=1 then for this PARAM then AVAL=1; Otherwise if PARAMCD in ("TRANSHY", "BILIHY", "ALPHY") then AVAL=0. If the visit is within 5-day window to previous visits then use the maximum R2ANRHI from visits within the 5-day window per each parameter.

variables.derivation: For a given parameter, set to AVAL when ABLFL='Y' and retain the BASE value in the parameter.

variables.name: CRIT1FL
variables.label: Criterion 1 Evaluation Result Flag
variables.derivation:
If PARAMCD in ("ALT", "AST") then calculate R2ANRHI = AVAL/ANRHI.
CRIT1FL = "Y" if R2ANRHI >=3; Else CRIT1FL = "N" if R2ANRHI is not missing; Else set CRIT1FL to null.

variables.name: CRIT2FL
variables.label: Criterion 2 Evaluation Result Flag
variables.derivation:
If PARAMCD in ("ALT", "AST") then calculate R2ANRHI = AVAL/ANRHI.
CRIT2FL = "Y" if R2ANRHI >=5; Else CRIT2FL = "N" if R2ANRHI is not missing; Else set CRIT2FL to null.

variables.name: CRIT3FL
variables.label: Criterion 3 Evaluation Result Flag
variables.derivation:
If PARAMCD in ("ALT", "AST") then calculate R2ANRHI = AVAL/ANRHI.
CRIT3FL = 'Y' if R2ANRHI >=10; Else CRIT3FL = 'N' if R2ANRHI is not missing; Else set CRIT3FL to null.

variables.name: CRIT4FL
variables.label: Criterion 4 Evaluation Result Flag
variables.derivation:
If PARAMCD in ("ALT", "AST") then calculate R2ANRHI = AVAL/ANRHI.
CRIT4FL = "Y" if R2ANRHI >=20; Else CRIT4FL = "N" if R2ANRHI is not missing; Else set CRIT4FL to null.

variables.name: CRIT5FL
variables.label: Criterion 5 Evaluation Result Flag
variables.derivation:
If PARAMCD = "BILI" then calculate R2ANRHI = AVAL/ANRHI.
CRIT5FL = "Y" if R2ANRHI >=1.5; Else CRIT5FL = "N" if R2ANRHI is not missing; Else set CRIT5FL to null.

variables.name: ANL01FL
variables.label: Analysis Flag 01
variables.derivation:
ANL01FL = "Y" for the record to be included in a per visit analysis. If there are multiple records within the visit window for an AVISIT then follow the rules in the SAP as: 
1. Select the measurement that is closest to the target day of the visit. If two measurements have the same distance from the target day then choose the mesurement prior to the target day. 
2. If there are multiple assessments on the same date, select the assessment at the scheduled visit cycle. Otherwise take the assessment in this order: End of Treatment visit > Safety Follow-up >  Unscheduled visit.
ANL01FL = "Y" should only be applied to baseline and post-baseline measurements up to 30 days after the Date of Last Exposure to Treatment or the day before initiation of subsequent anticancer therapy, whichever comes first.

variables.name: ANL02FL
variables.label: Analysis Flag 02
variables.derivation: Set to Y if the record is baseline or postbaseline records until the new anticancer therapy or treatment end day + 30 whichever occurs first

variables.name: AVALC
variables.label: Analysis Value (C)
variables.derivation:
Set to best response by IRC prior to or on the earlier date of (first PD date by IRC, initiation date of subsequent anticancer therapy). Based on RS.RSSTRESC where RSSTAT is not "NOT DONE" and RS.RSTESTCD = "OVRLRESP" and RS.RSCAT = "RECIST 1.1" and RS.RSEVAL = "INDEPENDENT ASSESSOR" and (RS.RSACPTFL = "Y" or RS.RSEVALID = "IR1" if Accepted Record Flag is null). Select the record with best response in order as CR>PR>SD>PD>NE. For subjects without target lesion at baseline, set to NE. For subjects without post-baseline assessments, set to "NA".
For SD as best response, it must also meet the protocol specified minimum time from baseline (>=42 days from 1st dose date). If the minimum time is not met, the subject’s best response depends on the subsequent assessments following SD. For example, if a subject had SD at first assessment, PD at second and did not meet minimum duration for SD, the subject's best response would be PD. If a subject lost to follow-up after the first SD assessment, the best response would be "NE".

variables.name: AVALC
variables.label: Analysis Value (C)
variables.derivation:
Set to best response by INV prior to or on the earlier date of (first PD date by INV, initiation date of subsequent anticancer therapy). Based on RS.RSSTRESC where RSSTAT is not "NOT DONE" and RSTESTCD = "OVRLRESP" and RSCAT = "RECIST 1.1" and RSEVAL = "INVESTIGATOR" and RSSTRESC is not missing. Select the record with best response in order as CR>PR>SD>PD>NE. For subjects without target lesion at baseline, set to "NE". For subjects without post-baseline assessments, set to "NA".
For SD as best response, it must also meet the protocol specified minimum time from baseline (>=42 days from 1st dose date). If the minimum time is not met, the subject’s best response depends on the subsequent assessments following SD. For example, if a subject had SD at first assessment, PD at second and did not meet minimum duration for SD, the subject's best response would be PD. If a subject lost to follow-up after the first SD assessment, then the best response would be "NE".

variables.name: AVALC
variables.label: Analysis Value (C)
variables.derivation:
Set to ADTUMOR.AVALC where ADTUMOR.PARAMCD = "IRCOVRSP" for record with the earliest Intracranial PD per the algorithm described in ADEFF.ADT where ADEFF.PARAMCD = "IRCFCNPD".
Intracranial progression is derived using the IRC tumor assessment based on RECIST 1.1 as any of the following:
a) New lesion(s) in the brain was unequivocally identified and the timepoint overall response was "Progressive Disease" (PD).
b) Non-target lesion(s) in the brain progressed, and the timepoint overall response was "Progressive Disease" (PD).
Intracranial lesion defined as ADTUMOR.TRLOC contains "BRAIN" or ADTUMOR.TRLOCSP contains "BRAIN".

variables.name: AVALC
variables.label: Analysis Value (C)
variables.derivation:
Only derive for subjects who were included in ITT population at IA. 
Set to ADTUMOR.AVALC where ADTUMOR.PARAMCD = "IRCOVRSP" for record with the earliest Intracranial PD per the algorithm described in ADEFF.ADT where ADEFF.PARAMCD = "IAIRCNPD". 
Intracranial Progresssion is derived using the IRC tumor assessments based on RECIST 1.1 as any of the following;
a) New lesion(s) in the brain was unequivocally identified and the timepoint overall response was "Progressive Disease" (PD). 
b) Non-target lesion(s) in the brain progressed, and the timepoint of the overall response was "Progressive Disease" (PD). 
Intracranial lesion is defined as ADTUMOR.TRLOC contains "BRAIN" or ADTUMOR.TRLOCSP contains "BRAIN".

variables.label: Analysis Value (C)
variables.derivation:
Set to ADTUMOR.AVALC where ADTUMOR.PARAMCD = "INVOVRSP" for the record with last INV evaluable response assessment on or prior to to the 231th PFS events date based on investigator assessment.
If the overall response is "CR", "PR", "SD", "PD", or "NON-CR/NON-PD", then it is considered as an evaluable response assessment.

If intracranial response is PD, then assign the earliest ADTUMOR.ADT of intracranial non-target progressed lesion or new intracranial lesion as the assessment date for the visit. 
Response is based on data from ADTUMOR.AVALC where ADTUMOR.PARAMCD = "IRCOVRSP" and satisfy any intracranial progression condition as following:
a) new lesion(s) in the brain was unequivocally identified and the timepoint overall response was "Progressive Disease" (PD).
b) Non-target lesion(s) in the brain progressed, and timepoint overall response was "Progressive Disease" (PD). 
Set to the assessment date at the visit with the first intracranial PD.

variables.name: ADT
variables.label: Analysis Date
variables.derivation:
For subjects who had PFS events (IRC PD or Death, whichever is earlier) immediately after 2 or more consecutive missed tumor assessments, then set to the date of the last IRC evaluable tumor assessment prior to PFS event as ADEFF.ADT where ADEFF.PARAMCD = "IRCLRSBP"; else set to ADTTE.ADT where ADTTE.PARAMCD = "PFSIRC".
Use the rules below to identify "missing 2+ consecutive tumor assessments":
For PD event:
1. If Analysis Relative Day of last tumor assessment before the PD date < (42-1)x7 and (PD date - last tumor assessment date prior PD +1) > (6+1+6+1+6+1)x7.
2. If (42-1)x7 <= Analysis Relative Day of last tumor assessment before the PD date <  (48-1)x7 and (PD date - last tumor assessment date prior PD +1) > (6+1+6+1+12+1)x7.
3. If (48-1)x7 <= Analysis Relative Day of last tumor assessment before the PD date < (54-1)x7 and (PD date - last tumor assessment date prior PD +1) > (6+1+12+1+12+1)x7. 
4. If Analysis Relative Day of last tumor assessment before the PD date >= (54-1)x7 and (PD date - last tumor assessment date prior PD +1) > (12+1+12+1+12+1)x7. 
5. If last tumor assessment before the PD date is missing and (PD date - last tumor assessment date prior PD +1) > 98 (day).
For Death event:
6. If Analysis Relative Day of last tumor assessment before death date < (48-1)x7 and (death date - last tumor assessment date prior death) > (6+1+6+1)x7.
7. If (54-1)x7 (day) > Analysis Relative Day of last tumor assessment before the death date >= (48-1)x7 and (death date - last tumor assessment date prior death) > (6+1+12+1)x7.
8. If Analysis Relative Day of last tumor assessment before the death date  >= (54-1)x7 and (death date - last tumor assessment date prior death) > (12+1+12+1)x7.
9. If last tumor assessment before the PFS event PD date is missing and (death date - last tumor assessment date prior death +1) > (6+1+6+1)x7.

For subjects who received subsequent anticancer therapy: if the first IRC PD date is on or prior to the initiation date of subsequent anticancer therapy then set to ADTTE.ADT where ADTTE.PARAMCD = "PFSIRC"; else set to the date of the last evaluable IRC response assessment which is prior to or on the initiation date of subsequent anticancer therapy as ADEFF.ADT where ADEFF.PARAMCD = "IRCLRSBT". 
Else set to randomization date ADSL.RANDDT.

For subjects who received subsequent anticancer therapy: if the first INV PD date is on or prior to the initiation date of subsequent anticancer therapy then set to ADTTE.ADT where ADTTE.PARAMCD = "PFSINV"; else set to the date of the last evaluable INV response assessment which is prior to or on the initiation date of subsequent anticancer therapy as ADEFF.ADT where ADEFF.PARAMCD = "INVLRSBT". 
Else set to randomization date ADSL.RANDDT.

4. If Analysis Relative Day of last tumor assessment before the PD date >= (54-1)x7 and (PD date - last tumor assessment date prior PD +1) > (12+1+12+1+12+1)x7.
For Death event:
5. If Analysis Relative Day of last tumor assessment before death date < (48-1)x7 and (death date - last tumor assessment date prior death +1) > (6+1+6+1)x7.
6. If (54-1)x7 > Analysis Relative Day of last tumor assessment before the death date >= (48-1)x7 and (death date - last tumor assessment date prior eath +1) > (6+1+12+1)x7. 
7. If Analysis Relative Day of last tumor assessment before death date >= (54-1)x7 and (death date - last tumor assessment date prior death +1) > (12+1+12+1)x7.

variables.name: ADT
variables.label: Analysis Date
variables.derivation:
Only derive for subjects who were included in ITT population at IA. 
For subjects who did not receive subsequent anticancer therapy on or prior to IA data extract date, set to ADTTE.ADT where ADTTE.PARAMCD = "PFSIRCIA".
For subjects who received subsequent anticancer therapy on or prior to IA data extract date: if first IRC PD date <= subsequent anticancer therapy start date, set to ADTTE.ADT where PARAMCD=’PFSIRCIA’; else set to ADEFF.ADT where PARAMCD='IAIRCLRT' (last evaluable IRC response assessment prior to or on subsequent anticancer therapy start date) if ADT is not missing; else set to randomization date (ADSL.RANDDT).

variables.name: ADT
variables.label: Analysis Date
variables.derivation:
Only derive for subjects who were included in ITT population at IA. 
For subjects who had PFS event (IRC PD or Death, whichever is earlier) on or prior to IA data extract date: If the PFS event was immediately after 2 or more consecutive missed tumor assessments and/or the PFS event was after initiating subsequent anticancer therapy, set to date of last IRC evaluable tumor assessment prior to PFS event (ADEFF.ADT where ADEFF.PARAMCD = "IAIRCLRP"), or date of last IRC evaluable tumor assessment on or prior to the initiation date of subsequent anticancer therapy (ADEFF.ADT where ADEFF.PARAMCD = "IAIRCLRT"); Else set to ADTTE.ADT where ADTTE.PARAMCD = "PFSIRCIA".
For subjects who did not have PFS event on or prior to IA data extract date: If subject received subsequent anticancer therapy then set to date of last IRC evaluable tumor assessment on or prior to initiation date of subsequent anticancer therapy (ADTTE.ADT where ADTTE.PARAMCD = "SA2IRCIA"); Else set to ADTTE.ADT where ADTTE.PARAMCD = "PFSIRCIA".

variables.name: ADT
variables.label: Analysis Date

If subject had IRC intracranial PD prior to IA-Cut then set to first intracranial PD date (ADEFF.ADT where ADEFF.PARAMCD = "IAIRCNPD"); else if subject died then set to death date (ADSL.IADTHDT); else if subject had post-baseline IRC response assessment then set to date of last evaluable IRC response assessment prior to IA-Cut (ADEFF.ADT where ADEFF.PARAMCD = "IAIRCLSR"); else set to randomization date (ADSL.RANDDT).

variables.name: CNSR
variables.label: Censor
variables.derivation:
Set to 0 if subject had intracranial progression or death, regardless of the use of subsequent anti-cancer therapy; set to 1 otherwise. 
Intracranial progression is derived using the IRC tumor assessment based on RECIST 1.1 as any of the following: a)  New lesion(s) in the brain was unequivocally identified and the timepoint overall response was "Progressive Disease" (PD); b) Non-target lesion(s) in the brain progressed, and the timepoint overall response was "Progressive Disease" (PD).

For subjects who received subsequent anticancer therapy:
For subjects who had PFS event: if the PFS event date was immediately after 2 or more consecutive missed tumor assessments and/or after the initiation date of subsequent anticancer therapy, then set to 1 (Censored); Else if the PFS event date was on or prior to the initiation date of subsequent anticancer therapy and without 2 or more consecutive missed tumor assessments immediately before the PFS event, then set to 0 (Event); Else for subjects who did not have PFS events, set to 1 (Censored).

variables.derivation: Only derive for responders by IRC. Set to date of initial response by IRC, which is ADEFF.ADT where ADEFF.PARAMCD = "IRCORR" and ADEFF.AVALC = "Y".

variables.name: STARTDT
variables.label: Time-to-Event Origin Date for Subject
variables.derivation: Only derive for responders by INV. Set to date of initial response by INV, which is ADEFF.ADT where ADEFF.PARAMCD = "INVORR" and ADEFF.AVALC = "Y".

variables.name: BASE
variables.label: Baseline Value
variables.derivation: For a given parameter, set to the last non-missing AVAL prior to the first dosing date and retain the BASE value in the parameter.

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Name match in ADaM v1.3 (defined in ADLB) (88%)

variables.name: CHG
variables.label: Change from Baseline
variables.derivation: AVAL - BASE, for post baseline records (when AVAL and BASE are not missing).

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Name match in ADaM v1.3 (defined in ADLB) (88%)

variables.name: PCHG
variables.label: Percent Change from Baseline
variables.derivation: 100*(CHG/BASE), for post baseline records (when CHG is not missing and BASE>0).

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Name match in ADaM v1.3 (defined in ADLB) (88%)

variables.name: ABLFL
variables.label: Baseline Record Flag
variables.derivation: For a given parameter, for subjects who received at least one dose of study treatment, set ABLFL = "Y" to the last non-missing assessment prior to the first dosing date; else for subjects who were randomized but did not receive study treatment, set ABLFL = "Y" to the last non-missing assessment before or on the randomization date.

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Name match in ADaM v1.3 (defined in ADLB) (88%)

variables.name: ANL01FL
variables.label: Analysis Flag 01
variables.derivation:
ANL01FL = "Y" if the AVAL is to be included in a per visit analysis. If multiple records for the same subject and parameter that have the same value of AVISIT then set ANL01FL = "Y" following the rule in the SAP as: 
1. Select the measurement with closest to the target study day. If multiple measurements are the same distance from the target day for a particular analysis window the mesurement prior to the target day will be chosen. 
2. If there are multiple assessments taken on the same date or same date and time, First take the assessment from the scheduled visit, then take the assessment from the End of Treatment visit, then from Safety Follow-up visit, then Unscheduled visit.

variables.name: ANL02FL
variables.label: Analysis Flag 02
variables.derivation: Subset to ADQS.PARCAT1 = "ECOG", set ANL02FL = "Y" for records with assessment date from start of the study treatment upto 30 days post treatment or 1 day before New Anticancer therapy whichever occur first; set ANL02FL = "Y" to Baseline assessments.

variables.name: ADT
variables.label: Analysis Date
variables.derivation:
If a subject has clinically meaningful deterioration or death then set to min of date of 1st deterioration or death. 
A clinically meaningful change is defined as a decrease for global health scale/QoL and functional scales or an increase for symptom scales/items in the score from baseline of ≥10.

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Name match in ADaM v1.3 (defined in ADLB) (88%)

variables.name: ADY
variables.label: Analysis Relative Day
variables.derivation: ADY = ADT - ADSL.TRTSDT +1 if ADT is not missing; else set to missing value.

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Name match in ADaM v1.3 (defined in ADLB) (88%)

variables.name: CNSR
variables.label: Censor
variables.derivation: AVAL = (ADT - STARTDT + 1)/30.4375 if ADT is not missing.

approval.comment: CDISC auto-approved: Name match in ADaM v1.3 (defined in ADLB) (88%)

variables.name: CNSDTDSC
variables.label: Censor Date Description
variables.derivation: If a subject had deterioration or died then set to null; else if a subject had post-baseline assessment(s) then set to the Last Assessment Date; else set to Date of Randomization (ADSL.RANDDT).
